President Donald Trump and First Lady Melania Trump expressed their condolences to the Bush family upon hearing of the passing of former President George H.W. Bush. They highlighted his love for his family and his dedication to serving the United States. They praised his service as a Naval Aviator in WWII, as well as his years in Congress, as a diplomat, CIA Director, and Vice President. They noted that his presidency left the country and the world in a more peaceful, prosperous, and secure state. The Trumps offered their prayers and deepest condolences to the Bush family and joined the American people in mourning the loss of this remarkable man. They believe that President Bush's example will continue to inspire and that his lifetime of service will always be remembered by the American people.